  :markdown-it
    ## Options
    
    Pass options to constructor to create new instance
    
    ```js
    let module = new Test({
      optionName: optionValue
    });
    ```
    
  p.api-item
    a.anchor(id='option-name', href='#option-name')
      include ./includes/anchor-icon.jade
    b.name name
    code String
    span.default default: 'Test'
    
  :markdown-it
    Specify the name of module.
  
    ## Instance Methods
  
    Invoke instance class method on SimpleModule instance:
  
    ```js
    let module = new Test()
    module.instanceMethod()
    ```
      
  p.api-item
    a.anchor(id='instance-method-name', href='#instance-method-name')
      include ./includes/anchor-icon.jade
    b.name name
    span.params ([#[span.param name]#[code String]])
    span.return return: name / self
    
  :markdown-it
    Get or set name of the module.
    
  :markdown-it
    ## Class Methods
    
    Invoke methods on SimpleModule class:
    
    ```js
    Test.classMethod()
    ```
    
  p.api-item
    a.anchor(id='class-method-test', href='#instance-method-test')
      include ./includes/anchor-icon.jade
